invlpg semantics: evicts single TLB entry for page containing addr
TLB after invlpg: Entry 0 evicted, 63 others intact
3. TLB MISS entry was evicted by invlpg
When to use CR3 reload vs invlpg
TLB BEFORE CR3 reload (64 mixed entries)
mov cr3, new_pd_phys (or same value for flush-all)
TLB AFTER CR3 reload (non-global evicted, globals survive)
PAGE_GLOBAL Optimization: kernel pages survive context switches
Fully-associative: any entry holds any page translation
64 entries: L1 dTLB (Intel Core). L2 stlb: 512-4096 entries
TLB hit cost: 1 cycle. TLB miss: 20-50 cycle page table walk
NOT coherent with DRAM page tables SW must invalidate!
Coverage: 64 x 4KB = 256KB working set at zero translation cost
Frame_A may belong to another process
Bug surfaces far from this site
Instruction: invlpg m (operand = memory address, not value)
Surgical: only entry 0 evicted, 63 others untouched
Context switch to different process: mandatory (new PD physical addr)
Bulk PTE changes (>8 pages): cheaper than N x invlpg
Flush ALL including kernel: write same CR3 value
Global entries (PAGE_GLOBAL + CR4.PGE=1) SURVIVE all CR3 reloads
Direct cost: ~30 cycles for mov cr3 instruction
Indirect cost: cold TLB miss penalty on next ~60 unique page accesses
60 misses x 50 cycles = ~3000 cycles warmup overhead after switch
Set PAGE_GLOBAL (bit 8) on all kernel PTEs + enable CR4.PGE
Result: kernel TLB entries never flushed on process switch
Without GLOBAL: every context switch cold-walks all kernel PTEs
Linux uses this; KPTI (Meltdown fix 2018) deliberately breaks it
Core 0 TLB: Entry 0 evicted by local invlpg
IPI handler: invlpg 0x400000, write ACK to LAPIC
15 IPIs x ~500 cycles round-trip = 7500 cycles per shootdown
Linux flush_tlb_others() uses APIC broadcast IPI
Linux batches multiple PTE changes before single shootdown
KPTI (2018 Meltdown fix): CR3 swap per syscall = 2 shootdowns
Measured KPTI overhead: 5-30% on syscall-heavy workloads
3. Send IPI to cores 1,2,...N via LAPIC
4. Spin-wait for ACK from all remote cores
5. Resume only after all ACKs received
